    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nThe command `:{range}lua` currently executes the lua code in the selected range, whereas `:{range}lua {code}` executes `{code}`, but ignores the range. This MR wants to give the lua code access to this range.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nWe introduce a hidden local dict `ev` which contains miscellaneous data we want the lua code to have access to. For now this is just the start and end lines of the range (or -1 if no range is provided).\r\n\r\nWe are essentially turning `:1,2lua {code}` into\r\n```lua\r\nlocal ev = {\r\n  startline = 1,\r\n  endline = 2\r\n}\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere doesn't seem to be a way to provide local vars to a lua snippet purely via the C API, as per this thread from the lua users mailing list: http://lua-users.org/lists/lua-l/2009-03/msg00660.html \r\n\r\n### To Do\r\n- [x] Prepend local variable declaration to lua snippet\r\n- [x] Create dict containing the desired values and push it onto the stack\r\n- [x] Expose this local variable to tab completion for better usability\r\n- [x] Add tests\r\n\r\n### Open questions\r\nRight now I'm using a typval dict and pass that as an argument to `nlua_typval_exec` in order to get it on the stack. Maybe it is cleaner to create a C struct which represents the `ev` dict and extend the parameters of `nlua_typval_exec` to optionally take in such a struct. Then we could just assemble a lua table on the stack directly without going through the typval conversion.\r\n\r\ncloses #7177 ",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-26T16:18:01Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The one thing I am unsure about is how and when to construct the local environment on the lua stack. Right now I am setting up the ev table separately in two different locations (when executing :lua and when fetching command completions), so the two would have to be kept in sync when adding new fields.\r\n\r\nMaybe it makes sense to create a new struct in the executor.c that represents ev, and have a function that can take in that struct and construct a lua table from it. Then we would only have to modify this function",
